      },
      {
        "name": "David Pointcheval",
        "email": "pointcheval@cosmian",
        "affiliation": ""
      }
    ],
    "abstract": "The ETSI Technical Specification 104 015 proposes a framework to build Key Encapsulation Mechanisms (KEMs) with access policies and attributes, in the Ciphertext-Policy Attribute-Based Encryption (CP-ABE) vein. Several security guarantees and functionalities are claimed, such as pre-quantum and post-quantum hybridization to achieve security against Chosen-Ciphertext Attacks (CCA), anonymity, and traceability.\r\nIn this paper, we present a formal security analysis of a more generic construction, with application to the specific Covercrypt scheme, based on the pre-quantum ECDH and the post-quantum ML-KEM KEMs. We additionally provide an open-source library that implements the ETSI standard, in Rust, with high effiency.",
    "keywords": [
      "ABE",
      "Post-Quantum",
      "Hybrid",
      "Implementation"
    ],
